How it works
============
The process bin/buildLibrary is executed which collects the MP3 tag information and
deposits into the file htdocs/library.txt.  For large MP3 collections this greater improves
performance but need to be run perdiocally to keep the data file up-to-date.  This can be
accomplished via a cron task.

Scheduling the library builder
The file format for the htdocs/playlists.txt is:
<Title>|<Type>|<PathOrExpr>

Title      : AlphaNumeric (sans '|')
Type       : 'm3u' or 'search' or 'search2' or #.*
PathOrExpr : <Path> or <SearchExpr> or <Search2Expr>
Path       : m3u file URL
SearchExpr : simple any/all field search string (e.g. 'Beatles')
Search2Expr: advanced search string (e.g. '? artist is Beatles and album has White')

If the first character for the type field is '#' the entry is ignored